net.doo.snap.mrzscanner

Class MRZScannerFrameHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.doo.snap.mrzscanner.MRZScannerFrameHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PreviewBuffer.FrameHandler

    public class MRZScannerFrameHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements PreviewBuffer.FrameHandler
    Performs MRZ data detection on camera preview frames. Outputs results via MRZScannerFrameHandler.ResultHandler (addResultHandler(ResultHandler)).

    Preview frame considered intercepted if at least one MRZScannerFrameHandler.ResultHandler returns true from MRZScannerFrameHandler.ResultHandler.handleResult(io.scanbot.mrzscanner.model.MRZRecognitionResult)

    See Also:

      • handleFrame

        public boolean handleFrame(byte[] frame,
                           int width,
                           int height,
                           int frameOrientation,
                           Rect finderRect)
        Description copied from interface: PreviewBuffer.FrameHandler
        Invoked for every new camera preview frame
        Specified by:
        handleFrame in interface PreviewBuffer.FrameHandler
        Parameters:
        frame - image in NV21 format
        width - width of the image
        height - height of the image
        frameOrientation - orientation of the image (in degrees)
        finderRect - finder overlay area
        Returns:
        true if frame should be considered as "intercepted", i.e. no further processing should be performed on it. false to allow other frame handlers to process this frame.

      • addResultHandler

        public void addResultHandler(MRZScannerFrameHandler.ResultHandler handler)
        Registers result handler which will be notified about MRZ data detection results.

        Results are coming on the worker thread. Don't forget to move execution to main thread before updating UI.

        Parameters:
        handler - handler to register. Must not be null. If handler was already registered, nothing happens.

      • removeResultHandler

        public void removeResultHandler(MRZScannerFrameHandler.ResultHandler handler)
        Unregisters handler.
        Parameters:
        handler - handler to unregister. If it was not registered before, nothing happens.

      • isEnabled

        public boolean isEnabled()
        Returns:
        true if MRZ data detection is enabled. false if MRZ data detection is disabled, i.e. incoming frames are skipped.

      • setEnabled

        public void setEnabled(boolean enabled)
        Parameters:
